Chinese President Xi Jinping on Thursday agreed in principle to accept the invitation from Japanese Prime Minister Shinzo Abe to pay a state visit to Japan in spring next year. The two leaders held a meeting ahead of a summit of the Group of 20 (G20) major economies slated for Friday and Saturday in the Japanese city of Osaka. 
